article.headline: Siena 74, Canisius 57
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Alex Franklin scored 26 points and Ryan Rossiter had 15 points and 17 rebounds as Siena defeated Canisius 74-57 victory on Sunday. Franklin was 11-for-16 from the field and the Saints (22-5, 15-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) shot 54.4 percent (31 of 57) to win for the 16th time in 17 games. Siena, which has clinched the MAAC regular-season title, closed the first half on a 10-0 run to take a 36-26 lead. Rossiter scored four points, Kyle Griffin hit a 3-pointer and O.D. Anosike converted a three-point play as the Saints built a lead they wouldn't relinquish. Franklin scored two layups during an 8-3 stretch that gave Siena a 68-51 lead with 4:15 remaining. Clarence Jackson added 16 points for the Saints, who completed a season sweep of Canisius (12-15, 7-9). Bob Bevilacqua scored 17 points and Frank Turner had 15 points and nine assists for Canisius.
